11171 /******************************************************************************/
11172 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
11173 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
11174 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
11175 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
11176 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
11177 /******************************************************************************/
11178

11181 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
11182 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
11183 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
11184 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
11185 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
11186 #define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
11187 #define USART3_6_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
11188 #define USART3_8_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
11189 #define PVD_IRQn VDDIO2_IRQn
11190 #define PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn VDDIO2_IRQn
11191 
11192 
11193 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */

11195 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler

11198 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler
11199 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
11200 #define TIM6_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler
